<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="10" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,1399,721,959]" lastBlockId="9.[189,1399,267,505]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="10" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
This pantropical genus comprises almost 25 species which are mostly terrestrial (and a few epiphytic) ferns displaying erect, large, highly-divided fronds on a short-creeping (or long-creeping in some Asiatic species) to erect stout rhizomes bearing numerous robust roots (
<figureCitation box="[1018,1090,791,817]" captionStart="Fig. 4" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1887,1913]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,1000,1847]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[189,1399,1000,1847]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 4. Terrestrial Comorian Hymenophyllaceae. A. Abrodictyum pseudorigidum Bauret &amp; Dubuisson, first identified as A. rigidum (Sw.) Ebihara &amp; Dubuisson, (F. Rakotondrainibe et al. 6771, P 00312031). B. Trichomanes boivinii Bosch, new for the archipelago according to the last inventories (as discussed in text) (F. Rakotondrainibe et al. 6675, P 00311390). Scale bar for both species = 3 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/896411/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). All Comorian specimens represent only one species although they are identified as either 
<taxonomicName authority="(Sw.) Ebihara &amp; Dubuisson" authorityName="(Sw.) Ebihara &amp; Dubuisson" box="[941,1398,826,853]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Abrodictyum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rigidum">
<emphasis box="[941,1067,826,853]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">A. rigidum</emphasis>
(Sw.) Ebihara &amp; Dubuisson
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName authority="(Desv.) Ebihara &amp; Dubuisson. These" authorityName="(Desv.) Ebihara &amp; Dubuisson. These" box="[224,863,862,888]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Trichomanes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cupressoides">
<emphasis box="[224,409,862,888]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">A. cupressoides</emphasis>
(Desv.) Ebihara &amp; Dubuisson. These
</taxonomicName>
two species are indeed commonly confused in collections. 
<bibRefCitation author="Kuhn F. A. M." box="[377,536,897,924]" journalOrPublisher="Engelman, Leipzig" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refString="Kuhn F. A. M. 1868. Filices Africanae. Engelman, Leipzig." title="Filices Africanae" type="book" year="1868">Kuhn (1868)</bibRefCitation>
also cited 
<taxonomicName authority="Blume" authorityName="Blume" authorityYear="1828" box="[685,1060,897,923]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Trichomanes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="obscurum">
<emphasis box="[685,967,897,923]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Trichomanes obscurum</emphasis>
Blume
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName authority="(Blume) Ebihara &amp; K. Iwats." authorityName="(Blume) Ebihara &amp; K.Iwats." class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Abrodictyum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="obscurum">
<emphasis box="[1117,1399,897,923]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Abrodictyum obscurum</emphasis>
(Blume) Ebihara &amp; K.Iwats.
</taxonomicName>
) for Mayotte, but this species is in fact restricted to Asia and is clearly distinct even if also often confused with 
<taxonomicName box="[703,834,267,294]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Abrodictyum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rigidum">
<emphasis box="[703,834,267,294]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">A. rigidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Recent morphological and molecular studies focused on 
<taxonomicName box="[327,510,303,329]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Trichomanes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cupressoides">
<emphasis box="[327,510,303,329]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">A. cupressoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and paleotropical 
<taxonomicName box="[732,859,303,329]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Abrodictyum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rigidum">
<emphasis box="[732,859,303,329]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">A. rigidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
evidenced that 
<taxonomicName box="[1047,1231,303,329]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Trichomanes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cupressoides">
<emphasis box="[1047,1231,303,329]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">A. cupressoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to Seychelles and is in fact nested within the distinct genus 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bauret et al. 2015)" authorityName="Bauret et al." authorityYear="2015" box="[848,1237,338,365]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Trichomanes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[848,1000,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Trichomanes</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bauret L. &amp; Grall A. &amp; Senterre B. &amp; Rouhan G. &amp; Hennequin S. &amp; Ebihara A. &amp; Dubuisson J. - Y." box="[1014,1229,338,365]" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="1 - 14" part="202" publicationUrl="http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.202.1.1" refString="Bauret L., Grall A., Senterre B., Rouhan G., Hennequin S., Ebihara A. &amp; Dubuisson J. - Y. 2015. New circumscription of Trichomanes cupressoides Desvaux (Hymenophyllaceae), an endemic filmy fern from Seychelles (Indian Ocean), and new insights into the genus Abrodictyum C. Presl in the western Indian Ocean. Phytotaxa 202: 1 - 14. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 202.1.1" title="New circumscription of Trichomanes cupressoides Desvaux (Hymenophyllaceae), an endemic filmy fern from Seychelles (Indian Ocean), and new insights into the genus Abrodictyum C. Presl in the western Indian Ocean" type="journal article" year="2015">
Bauret 
<emphasis box="[1100,1158,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">et al.</emphasis>
2015
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Desv." authorityName="Desv." class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Trichomanes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cupressoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Trichomanes cupressoides</emphasis>
Desv.
</taxonomicName>
is thus absent from Comoros. Furthermore, specimens of the Malagasy region (including Comoros) formerly identified as 
<taxonomicName box="[698,823,408,435]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Abrodictyum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rigidum">
<emphasis box="[698,823,408,435]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">A. rigidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
actually represent a distinct species from the true neotropical 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bauret et al. 2015)" authorityName="Bauret et al." authorityYear="2015" box="[327,688,443,470]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Abrodictyum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rigidum">
<emphasis box="[327,452,443,470]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">A. rigidum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bauret L. &amp; Grall A. &amp; Senterre B. &amp; Rouhan G. &amp; Hennequin S. &amp; Ebihara A. &amp; Dubuisson J. - Y." box="[466,680,443,470]" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="1 - 14" part="202" publicationUrl="http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.202.1.1" refString="Bauret L., Grall A., Senterre B., Rouhan G., Hennequin S., Ebihara A. &amp; Dubuisson J. - Y. 2015. New circumscription of Trichomanes cupressoides Desvaux (Hymenophyllaceae), an endemic filmy fern from Seychelles (Indian Ocean), and new insights into the genus Abrodictyum C. Presl in the western Indian Ocean. Phytotaxa 202: 1 - 14. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 202.1.1" title="New circumscription of Trichomanes cupressoides Desvaux (Hymenophyllaceae), an endemic filmy fern from Seychelles (Indian Ocean), and new insights into the genus Abrodictyum C. Presl in the western Indian Ocean" type="journal article" year="2015">
Bauret 
<emphasis box="[553,611,443,469]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">et al.</emphasis>
2015
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, and this new species has recently been described and named 
<taxonomicName authority="Bauret &amp; Dubuisson (Dubuisson et al. 2016)" authorityName="Bauret &amp; Dubuisson (Dubuisson et al." authorityYear="2016" box="[189,1056,478,505]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Abrodictyum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pseudorigidum">
<emphasis box="[189,523,479,505]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Abrodictyum pseudorigidum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Dubuisson J. - Y. &amp; Bauret L. &amp; Grall A. &amp; Li T. &amp; Ebihara A. &amp; Hennequin S." box="[530,1056,478,505]" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="151 - 168" part="284" publicationUrl="http://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.284.3.1" refString="Dubuisson J. - Y., Bauret L., Grall A., Li T., Ebihara A. &amp; Hennequin S. 2016. Discussion on the taxonomy of African fern Abrodictyum rigidum (Sw.) Ebihara &amp; Dubuisson and description of two new Abrodictyum C. Presl species (Hymenophyllaceae, Polypodiidae) for the Afro-Malagasy region. Phytotaxa 284: 151 - 168. http: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 284.3.1" title="Discussion on the taxonomy of African fern Abrodictyum rigidum (Sw.) Ebihara &amp; Dubuisson and description of two new Abrodictyum C. Presl species (Hymenophyllaceae, Polypodiidae) for the Afro-Malagasy region" type="journal article" year="2016">
Bauret &amp; Dubuisson (Dubuisson 
<emphasis box="[921,980,479,505]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">et al.</emphasis>
2016)
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
